1 a.definition: to submit (a legal document) to the proper office (as the office of a clerk of court) for keeping on file among the records esp. as a procedural step in a legal transaction or proceeding [a tax return] [a financing statementwith the Secretary of State] [a notice of appeal][a mortgage in the Registry of Deeds]

sub_terms.b: to place (as a document) on file among the records of an office esp. by formally receiving and endorsing [a complaintby the clerk despite the absence of the filing fee]

1 a.note: In nearly all cases, a document is deemed to be filed when it is actually received by the office to which it is directed. A few cases, however, have held that a document is filed upon the mailing of it.
1 a.filed: by the clerk despite the absence of the filing fee]
